{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1270,"text":"Will we do whatever it takes\nto tackle climate change?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":7393,"text":"I come at this question\nnot as a green campaigner,"},{"time":10390,"text":"in fact, I confess to be rather\nhopeless at recycling."},{"time":13404,"text":"I come at it as a professional observer\nof financial policy making"},{"time":18693,"text":"and someone that wonders\nhow history will judge us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24353,"text":"One day,"},{"time":25633,"text":"this ring that belonged to my grandfather"},{"time":29522,"text":"will pass to my son, Charlie."},{"time":32021,"text":"And I wonder what his generation"},{"time":34853,"text":"and perhaps the one that follows"},{"time":37183,"text":"will make of the two lives\nthis ring has worked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42995,"text":"My grandfather was a coal miner."},{"time":46500,"text":"In his time,"},{"time":48616,"text":"burning fossil fuels for energy\nand for allowing economies to develop"},{"time":53609,"text":"was accepted."},{"time":55198,"text":"We know now that that is not the case"},{"time":58601,"text":"because of the greenhouse\ngases that coal produces."},{"time":63315,"text":"But today,"},{"time":64556,"text":"I fear it's the industry in which I work\nthat will be judged more harshly"},{"time":68626,"text":"because of its impact on the climate --"},{"time":71498,"text":"more harshly than\nmy grandfather's industry, even."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74202,"text":"I work, of course,\nin the banking industry,"},{"time":76912,"text":"which will be remembered\nfor its crisis in 2008 --"},{"time":81831,"text":"a crisis that diverted the attention\nand finances of governments"},{"time":86746,"text":"away from some really, really\nimportant promises,"},{"time":92151,"text":"like promises made at the Copenhagen\nClimate Summit in 2009"},{"time":97315,"text":"to mobilize 100 billion dollars a year"},{"time":100171,"text":"to help developing countries\nmove away from burning fossil fuels"},{"time":104709,"text":"and transition to using cleaner energy."},{"time":108396,"text":"That promise is already in jeopardy."},{"time":111904,"text":"And that's a real problem,"},{"time":113793,"text":"because that transition\nto cleaner energy needs to happen"},{"time":116558,"text":"sooner rather than later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119184,"text":"Firstly,"},{"time":120364,"text":"because greenhouse gases, once released,"},{"time":122366,"text":"stay in the atmosphere for decades."},{"time":125083,"text":"And secondly,"},{"time":126295,"text":"if a developing economy builds\nits power grid around fossil fuels today,"},{"time":132146,"text":"it's going to be way more costly\nto change later on."},{"time":136316,"text":"So for the climate,"},{"time":138486,"text":"history may judge\nthat the banking crisis happened"},{"time":142336,"text":"at just the wrong time."},{"time":144920,"text":"The story need not be this gloomy, though."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149669,"text":"Three years ago,"},{"time":151601,"text":"I argued that governments\ncould use the tools"},{"time":154521,"text":"deployed to save the financial system"},{"time":157230,"text":"to meet other global challenges."},{"time":159918,"text":"And these arguments are getting\nstronger, not weaker, with time."},{"time":166334,"text":"Let's take a brief reminder\nof what those tools looked like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171578,"text":"When the financial crisis hit in 2008,"},{"time":174589,"text":"the central banks of the US and UK"},{"time":177190,"text":"began buying bonds issued\nby their own governments"},{"time":180649,"text":"in a policy known\nas \"quantitative easing.\""},{"time":183385,"text":"Depending on what happens\nto those bonds when they mature,"},{"time":187119,"text":"this is money printing by another name."},{"time":190350,"text":"And boy, did they print."},{"time":192784,"text":"The US alone created four trillion\ndollars' worth of its own currency."},{"time":197376,"text":"This was not done in isolation."},{"time":199489,"text":"In a remarkable act of cooperation,"},{"time":202187,"text":"the 188 countries that make up\nthe International Monetary Fund, the IMF,"},{"time":206784,"text":"agreed to issue 250 billion\ndollars' worth of their own currency --"},{"time":210977,"text":"the Special Drawing Right --"},{"time":213073,"text":"to boost reserves around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215712,"text":"When the financial crisis moved to Europe,"},{"time":219626,"text":"the European Central Bank\nPresident, Mario Draghi,"},{"time":223091,"text":"promised \"to do whatever it takes.\""},{"time":227516,"text":"And they did."},{"time":229696,"text":"The Bank of Japan repeated those words --\nthat exact same commitment --"},{"time":234074,"text":"to do \"whatever it takes\"\nto reflate their economy."},{"time":239484,"text":"In both cases,"},{"time":241400,"text":"\"whatever it takes\" meant\ntrillions of dollars more"},{"time":245663,"text":"in money-printing policies\nthat continue today."},{"time":249334,"text":"What this shows"},{"time":251146,"text":"is that when faced\nwith some global challenges,"},{"time":256062,"text":"policy makers are able to act\ncollectively, with urgency,"},{"time":260731,"text":"and run the risks of unconventional\npolicies like money printing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267509,"text":"So, let's go back\nto that original question:"},{"time":273511,"text":"Can we print money for climate finance?"},{"time":277201,"text":"Three years ago,"},{"time":278955,"text":"the idea of using money in this way\nwas something of a taboo."},{"time":282714,"text":"Once you break down and dismantle the idea"},{"time":285914,"text":"that money is a finite resource,"},{"time":288580,"text":"governments can quickly get overwhelmed\nby demands from their people"},{"time":293087,"text":"to print more and more\nmoney for other causes:"},{"time":296337,"text":"education, health care, welfare --"},{"time":298361,"text":"even defense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300384,"text":"And there are some truly terrible\nhistorical examples of money printing --"},{"time":305846,"text":"uncontrolled money printing --"},{"time":308193,"text":"leading to hyperinflation."},{"time":310764,"text":"Think: Weimar Republic in 1930;"},{"time":314374,"text":"Zimbabwe more recently, in 2008,"},{"time":317471,"text":"when the prices of basic goods\nlike bread are doubling every day."},{"time":322892,"text":"But all of this is moving\nthe public debate forward,"},{"time":327920,"text":"so much so, that money printing\nfor the people is now discussed openly"},{"time":333272,"text":"in the financial media, and even\nin some political manifestos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338203,"text":"But it's important the debate\ndoesn't stop here,"},{"time":340766,"text":"with printing national currencies."},{"time":345912,"text":"Because climate change\nis a shared global problem,"},{"time":349875,"text":"there are some really compelling reasons"},{"time":352969,"text":"why we should be printing\nthat international currency"},{"time":356422,"text":"that's issued by the IMF,"},{"time":358304,"text":"to fund it."},{"time":359944,"text":"The Special Drawing Right, or SDR,"},{"time":363173,"text":"is the IMF's electronic unit of account"},{"time":366553,"text":"that governments use to transfer\nfunds amongst each other."},{"time":371933,"text":"Think of it as a peer-to-peer\npayment network,"},{"time":374698,"text":"like Bitcoin, but for governments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378572,"text":"And it's truly global."},{"time":381005,"text":"Each of the 188 members\nof the IMF hold SDR quotas"},{"time":386301,"text":"as part of their foreign\nexchange reserves."},{"time":389935,"text":"These are national stores of wealth"},{"time":392247,"text":"that countries keep to protect\nthemselves against currency crises."},{"time":396764,"text":"And that global nature is why,"},{"time":399083,"text":"at the height of the financial\ncrisis in 2009,"},{"time":403410,"text":"the IMF issued those extra\n250 billion dollars --"},{"time":407152,"text":"because it served\nas a collective global action"},{"time":410747,"text":"that safeguarded countries\nlarge and small in one fell swoop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417043,"text":"But here --"},{"time":418363,"text":"here's the intriguing part."},{"time":421083,"text":"More than half of those extra SDRs\nthat were printed in 2009 --"},{"time":426309,"text":"150 billion dollars' worth --"},{"time":428319,"text":"went to developed market countries\nwho, for the most part,"},{"time":432658,"text":"have a modest need\nfor these foreign exchange reserves,"},{"time":435519,"text":"because they have flexible exchange rates."},{"time":438427,"text":"So those extra reserves\nthat were printed in 2009,"},{"time":442832,"text":"in the end, for developed\nmarket countries at least,"},{"time":446327,"text":"weren't really needed."},{"time":448508,"text":"And they remain unused today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451642,"text":"So here's an idea."},{"time":453026,"text":"As a first step,"},{"time":455046,"text":"why don't we start\nspending those unused,"},{"time":458136,"text":"those extra SDRs\nthat were printed in 2009,"},{"time":461627,"text":"to combat climate change?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":463948,"text":"They could, for example,"},{"time":465485,"text":"be used to buy bonds issued\nby the UN's Green Climate Fund."},{"time":470901,"text":"This was a fund created in 2009,"},{"time":473821,"text":"following that climate\nagreement in Copenhagen."},{"time":477906,"text":"And it was designed to channel funds\ntowards developing countries"},{"time":482286,"text":"to meet their climate projects."},{"time":484377,"text":"It's been one of the most\nsuccessful funds of its type,"},{"time":487260,"text":"raising almost 10 billion dollars."},{"time":489588,"text":"But if we use those extra\nSDRs that were issued,"},{"time":493050,"text":"it helps governments get back on track,"},{"time":496386,"text":"to meet that promise\nof 100 billion dollars a year"},{"time":499233,"text":"that was derailed by the financial crisis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503766,"text":"It could also --"},{"time":505698,"text":"it could also serve as a test case."},{"time":510096,"text":"If the inflationary consequences\nof using SDRs in this way are benign,"},{"time":516474,"text":"it could be used to justify"},{"time":518453,"text":"the additional, extra issuance\nof SDRs, say, every five years,"},{"time":523211,"text":"again, with the commitment"},{"time":525630,"text":"that developed-market countries\nwould direct their share"},{"time":530084,"text":"of the new reserves"},{"time":531569,"text":"to the Green Climate Fund."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535076,"text":"Printing international money\nin this way has several advantages"},{"time":538824,"text":"over printing national currencies."},{"time":541500,"text":"The first is it's really easy to argue"},{"time":544339,"text":"that spending money to mitigate\nclimate change benefits everyone."},{"time":549366,"text":"No one section of society benefits\nfrom the printing press over another."},{"time":553249,"text":"That problem of competing\nclaims is mitigated."},{"time":557463,"text":"It's also fair to say"},{"time":558827,"text":"that because it takes so many countries\nto agree to issue these extra SDRs,"},{"time":563978,"text":"it's highly unlikely that money printing\nwould get out of control."},{"time":568998,"text":"What you end up with\nis a collective, global action"},{"time":574881,"text":"aimed -- and it's controlled\nglobal action --"},{"time":578236,"text":"aimed at a global good."},{"time":581637,"text":"And,"},{"time":582869,"text":"as we've learned\nwith the money-printing schemes,"},{"time":585460,"text":"whatever concerns we have\ncan be allayed by rules."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588757,"text":"So, for example,"},{"time":590663,"text":"the issuance of these extra SDRs\nevery five years could be capped,"},{"time":595660,"text":"such that this international currency\nis never more than five percent"},{"time":601279,"text":"of global foreign exchange reserves."},{"time":603781,"text":"That's important because it would allay"},{"time":605830,"text":"well, let's say, the ridiculous\nconcerns that the US might have"},{"time":609750,"text":"that the SDR could ever challenge\nthe dollar's dominant role"},{"time":614296,"text":"in international finance."},{"time":616214,"text":"And in fact,"},{"time":618021,"text":"I think the only thing that the SDR\nwould likely steal from the dollar"},{"time":621439,"text":"under this scheme"},{"time":622932,"text":"is its nickname, the \"greenback.\""},{"time":626427,"text":"Because even with that cap in place,"},{"time":630367,"text":"the IMF could have\nfollowed up its issuance --"},{"time":633855,"text":"its massive issuance of SDRs in 2009 --"},{"time":636927,"text":"with a further 200 billion\ndollars of SDRs in 2014."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642716,"text":"So hypothetically,"},{"time":646052,"text":"that would mean that developed countries\ncould have contributed"},{"time":649194,"text":"up to 300 billion dollars' worth of SDRs"},{"time":653739,"text":"to the Green Climate Fund."},{"time":656186,"text":"That's 30 times what it has today."},{"time":659670,"text":"And you know,"},{"time":660850,"text":"as spectacular as that sounds,"},{"time":663580,"text":"it's only just beginning to look\nlike \"whatever it takes.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":669129,"text":"And just to think what amazing things\ncould be done with that money,"},{"time":672471,"text":"consider this:"},{"time":674618,"text":"in 2009,"},{"time":676270,"text":"Norway promised one billion dollars\nof its reserves to Brazil"},{"time":681032,"text":"if they followed through\non their goals on deforestation."},{"time":686593,"text":"That program has since delivered\na 70 percent reduction in deforestation"},{"time":692916,"text":"in the past decade."},{"time":694926,"text":"That's saving 3.2 billion tons\nof carbon dioxide emissions,"},{"time":699288,"text":"which is the equivalent of taking\nall American cars off the roads"},{"time":703843,"text":"for three whole years."},{"time":707704,"text":"So what could we do"},{"time":709030,"text":"with 300 other pay-for-performance\nclimate projects like that,"},{"time":714098,"text":"organized on a global scale?"},{"time":717937,"text":"We could take cars off the roads\nfor a generation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721384,"text":"So,"},{"time":723000,"text":"let's not quibble about whether we can\nafford to fund climate change."},{"time":728877,"text":"The real question is:"},{"time":731149,"text":"Do we care enough about future generations"},{"time":734570,"text":"to take the very same policy risks\nwe took to save the financial system?"},{"time":740223,"text":"After all,"},{"time":742249,"text":"we could do it,"},{"time":744284,"text":"we did do it"},{"time":745459,"text":"and we are doing it today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747808,"text":"We must, must, must do\n\"whatever it takes.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":753426,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754601,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}